9 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Ex parte extreme risk order of protection. (1) A petitioner may request
10 that an ex parte extreme risk order of protection be issued before a hearing for an extreme risk order of
11 protection, without notice to the respondent, by including in the petition detailed allegations based on personal
12 knowledge that the respondent poses a significant risk of causing personal injury to the respondent's self or
13 others in the near future by having custody or control of, purchasing, possessing, or receiving a firearm.
14 (2) In considering whether to issue an ex parte extreme risk order of protection under this section,
15 the court shall consider all relevant evidence, including the evidence described in [section 3].
16 (3) If a court finds there is good cause to believe that the respondent poses a significant risk of
17 causing personal injury to the respondent's self or others by having custody or control of, purchasing,
18 possessing, or receiving a firearm if the court does not act immediately, the court shall issue an ex parte
19 extreme risk order of protection.
20 (4) The court shall hold an ex parte extreme risk order of protection hearing in person or by
21 telephone or videoconference on the day the petition is filed or within 48 hours of the filing of the petition.
22 (5) In accordance with [section 3], the court shall schedule a hearing within 14 days after the
23 issuance of an ex parte extreme risk order of protection to determine if a 1-year extreme risk order of protection
24 should be issued under [sections 1 through 12].
25 (6) An ex parte extreme risk order of protection must include:
26 (a) a statement of the grounds asserted for the order;
27 (b) the date and time the order was issued;
